ENTRY       EC 1.14.99.44               Enzyme
NAME        diapolycopene oxygenase;
            crtP (ambiguous)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            Miscellaneous
SYSNAME     4,4'-diapolycopene,AH2:oxygen oxidoreductase (4,4'-hydroxylating)
REACTION    4,4'-diapolycopene + 4 AH2 + 4 O2 = 4,4'-diapolycopenedial + 4 A + 6 H2O [RN:R09671]
ALL_REAC    R09671;
            (other) R07654 R09727 R09728
SUBSTRATE   4,4'-diapolycopene [CPD:C19797];
            AH2 [CPD:C00030];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     4,4'-diapolycopenedial [CPD:C19798];
            A [CPD:C00028];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     Little activity with neurosporene or lycopene. Involved in the biosynthesis of C30 carotenoids such as staphyloxanthin. The enzyme oxidizes each 
            methyl group to the hydroxymethyl and then a dihydroxymethyl group, 
            followed by the spontaneous loss of water to give an aldehyde group.
